      <h2>Black Anchor</h2>
      <p>We love to inspire a lifestyle of lasting goods. Our hearts and hands are invested in designing products that are beautiful, durable, and able to narrate incredible stories it’s owner will live for generations to come - for all to share. Sustainability through design is not only our passion, but our lifestyle.</p>
      <p><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0211/0380/t/4/assets/stephen-and-ally-jones-black-anchor-workshop.jpg"></p>
      <p>My wife, Ally, and I find that together we are passionate about many things. We enjoy having few possessions, and having them be nice ones. We try to learn about the things that we come to own so that we can make them last as long as possible. When this is applied to what we create as Black Anchor, it means that we put as much time as we can in the quality of a piece. We want the pieces we create to be heritage pieces, not to end up in landfills, but to be passed along for generations.</p>
      <h2>Tacoma, WA</h2>
      <p>Our workshop is located in Tacoma, Washington. Also known as the Gritty Port City. The environment speaks volumes to the craft. The Northwest is unparalleled when it comes to culture and environmental beauty.</p>
      <p>You can think of Seattle, Portland, and Tacoma as three brothers. Seattle is the hipster who grew up and got a job, Portland is the freethinker who refuses to get a job, and Tacoma is the hardworking brother who always had a job. No offense to our brother cities. We think they’re both awesome in their own ways.</p>
      <p>But Tacoma is it for us. When our city’s blue-collar grit and artistic verve slam into each other awesome things are born. Our design aesthetic - rugged, simple, functional, beautiful - mirrors the city that we love and call home.</p>
      <h2>Values</h2>
      <h3>Function + Durability</h3>
      <p>We spend a lot of time living life here in the Great Northwest. We build our pieces with function and durability in mind, which means they’ll stand up to your adventures – and stand the test time.</p>
      <h3>Environment + Beauty</h3>
      <p>Our leather working employs natural, environmentally friendly processes like vegetable tanning. This process also makes leather age beautifully. So hopefully one day your Black Anchor Workshop wallet or belt will go to your great grandchild, not to a landfill.</p>
      <h3>Community + Creativity</h3>
      <p>More than anything, we love our friends and family. We also value the things that are created or curated by these people. We like to design products that tell more than our own story, but the story of those that we love and the things that they cherish.</p>
